places.address: FX5G+647 Jama Masjid, Hans Nagar, Sambalpur, Odisha 768001

featured_reviews.review_id:
It is located in Delhi, India.

Jama Masjid is one of the largest mosques in India.

It was built by Shah Jahan, a Mughal Emperor.

It was established in 1656.

Jama Masjid consists of 2 minarets each 40 meters high.

The mosque is made up of red sandstone and marble.

The mosque can hold a capacity of more than 25000 people.

There are 3 domes on the terrace of the mosque which are surrounded by the 2 minarets.

Jama Masjid is a magnificent place to visit and attracts a lot of tourists from everywhere.
